1
00:00:00,733 --> 00:00:03,833
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:09,933
Can you feel this?

3
00:00:10,067 --> 00:00:11,033
No.

4
00:00:11,167 --> 00:00:12,433
Can you feel this?

5
00:00:12,567 --> 00:00:13,567
I was the one who cheated.

6
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:14,900
I was the fool.

7
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:16,867
Why are my children
the ones being punished?

8
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,833
You still have a chance
to fix everything.

9
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,167
If it were not
because of you,

10
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:21,933
Ashley would not be
in this situation.

11
00:00:22,067 --> 00:00:25,367
Because every time I see Jasmine
strong and walking,

12
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,800
I feel like breaking down!

13
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:28,967
Please tell Edward
thank you very much.

14
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:30,567
Why are you thanking Edward?

15
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,033
Do you not know? He was the one
who convinced the board

16
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:36,333
- to replace Paolo.
- Do not help him, Regina.

17
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,300
Ashley's life
is at stake here.

18
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:39,800
My child's life.

19
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:41,200
Dad, you're heartless!

20
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,200
- Do you want to know why?
- I want to know!

21
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:44,600
Because I will not help someone

22
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:47,600
who should never have been part
of this family!

23
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:39,333
Why is it like this?

24
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:42,133
I was the one who cheated.

25
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:44,900
I was the one who messed up.

26
00:01:46,267 --> 00:01:48,367
Why are my children
the ones being punished?

27
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,367
It should have been me instead.

28
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,733
Paolo, enough.

29
00:01:53,933 --> 00:01:56,333
You still have a chance
to fix everything.

30
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:59,800
Did you not do everything
before for Jasmine?

31
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:02,267
This time, Ashley needs you.

32
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:05,433
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,067
You are right.

34
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,167
I will not abandon
my other child.

35
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,900
I will not let her spend
the rest of her life

36
00:02:16,967 --> 00:02:18,167
in a wheelchair.

37
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:28,233
You are being foolish.

38
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:29,967
What if something worse
happens to you

39
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:31,567
because of your fighting?

40
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:34,333
Then both you and Ashley
will be disabled.

41
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:36,600
Do you expect me to just
let Aldrin walk all over me?

42
00:02:36,733 --> 00:02:39,700
Forget Aldrin.
[SCOFFS]

43
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:43,267
I am sure Paolo will come
to us anytime soon

44
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:46,067
to cover all the expenses.

45
00:02:48,067 --> 00:02:49,067
What?

46
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:53,867
I met to Paolo and Marj.

47
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,333
I am making them pay
for Ashley's surgery.

48
00:02:58,433 --> 00:03:00,367
Why did you do that?

49
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:01,900
Did I not make myself clear?

50
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:03,933
I do not want to ask them
for help.

51
00:03:04,067 --> 00:03:05,400
I did not ask.

52
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:08,367
I demanded payment,
that is different.

53
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:10,500
You still went behind my back.

54
00:03:10,633 --> 00:03:13,200
Would you rather I did nothing?

55
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,333
If you have issues with them

56
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:17,533
and you refuse
to swallow your pride,

57
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:18,933
leave me out of it.

58
00:03:19,067 --> 00:03:21,233
I will do anything for Ashley.

59
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:24,033
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:25,567
Look at you.

61
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:28,733
You gained nothing
from the person you trusted.

62
00:03:28,867 --> 00:03:30,367
You were just scammed.

63
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:34,133
If I had not gone to Paolo,
we would still have nothing.

64
00:03:34,267 --> 00:03:37,867
So please, stop being dramatic.

65
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,967
Time is against us, Edward.

66
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:50,733
[MACHINE BEEPING]

67
00:03:59,167 --> 00:04:00,333
Hey, Ash.

68
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:02,400
I have a surprise for you.

69
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,600
- Ash, I missed you.
- Jas?

70
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:07,900
Auntie?

71
00:04:10,967 --> 00:04:13,400
I missed you too, Jas.

72
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:15,600
I am so happy
you are getting better.

73
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:18,033
Thanks to you.

74
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:21,533
I am so sorry, Ash.

75
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:24,967
- If not because of me...
- If not because of you,

76
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:27,867
Ashley would not be
in this situation.

77
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,200
Wait.

78
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:31,400
Who said you were allowed
to visit?

79
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:33,500
Mom, it is okay.

80
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:35,133
It is not okay with me!

81
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:36,633
Get out!

82
00:04:36,767 --> 00:04:40,933
Thea, can we please talk first
about Ashley's surgery?

83
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:42,367
I was very clear.

84
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:45,267
Give me what I am asking for
then we will talk.

85
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:48,833
But that does not mean
you have the right to defy me!

86
00:04:48,967 --> 00:04:51,900
Do not go near Ashley!

87
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:54,633
I am sorry.

88
00:04:54,767 --> 00:04:56,567
Thea, she just want to visit...

89
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,700
I do not care!

90
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,633
Xander, take them out.

91
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,900
I might lose my temper
even more.

92
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:05,133
Let's go.

93
00:05:09,733 --> 00:05:12,267
Mom, why did you do that?

94
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:16,433
Because every time I see Jasmine
strong and walking,

95
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,433
I feel like breaking down!

96
00:05:19,567 --> 00:05:21,267
They took your future away!

97
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:24,000
They robbed you
of a normal life!

98
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:32,300
So even if they beg,
I will not forgive them!

99
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:34,767
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:05:39,567 --> 00:05:42,200
<i>Sir Greg, why did you call us
here?</i>

101
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,333
I just spoke
to the investigator.

102
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,433
They still cannot locate Yolly.

103
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,133
You were close to her before,
right?

104
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:56,333
Maybe you have an idea
where she is.

105
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:01,233
We really do not know anything.

106
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:07,600
Since Ms. Yolly disappeared,
we have had no contact with her.

107
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:10,633
We are worried about her.

108
00:06:11,867 --> 00:06:13,067
Remember this.

109
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:18,033
Yolly burned the entire house
with all three of you inside!

110
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,000
If any of you were harmed,

111
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:24,333
any one of you,
it would be her fault.

112
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:27,567
So, speak if you know something.

113
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,800
Do not cover for her!

114
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,467
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,767
We truly have no idea.

116
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,533
Sir, we are sorry.

117
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:40,167
[SIGHS]

118
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,800
Is that Edward?

119
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:47,733
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:54,633
My child, I am so sorry
to hear about Ashley.

121
00:06:54,767 --> 00:06:56,367
My poor grandchild.

122
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,833
She does not deserve to suffer.

123
00:06:57,967 --> 00:06:59,333
She is such a kind child.

124
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:01,267
And very selfless.

125
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,567
Mom, she needs surgery
immediately.

126
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:07,400
If only I could ask someone
for help,

127
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:09,667
I would not bother you.

128
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,433
What are you saying?
I am your mother

129
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:12,800
and Ashley is my grandchild.

130
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:16,500
I will definitely help you,
okay?

131
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:18,900
You will not help him, Regina.

132
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:22,867
Are you serious, Greg?

133
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,733
Our child needs help.

134
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:30,633
Weng, take care of Jasmine
for now.

135
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:32,600
I do not have a child
who only comes to me

136
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:34,133
when they need something.

137
00:07:35,433 --> 00:07:36,500
Why, Edward?

138
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:39,367
Where did all
that confidence go?

139
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:44,267
Where's that pride you had
about not needing us?

140
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,000
Dad...

141
00:07:46,133 --> 00:07:47,733
this is for my child.

142
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:49,167
Not for me.

143
00:07:50,767 --> 00:07:52,367
Then be a father.

144
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,800
Find your own money!

145
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,600
Regina,

146
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:59,233
do not give him anything!

147
00:07:59,367 --> 00:08:03,067
If you help him,
you will answer to me.

148
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,533
You are going too far, Greg.

149
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,667
Have mercy on your child.

150
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,767
Have mercy on Ashley.

151
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:12,367
Leave now!

152
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,500
Before I have you dragged out
by the guards.

153
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:16,100
Leave now.

154
00:08:16,233 --> 00:08:18,967
- Leave now!
- Greg, what are you doing?

155
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:24,467
You know what hurts the most,
Dad?

156
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:27,467
It's not you refusing
to help me.

157
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:31,033
But you treating me like dirt
on your shoe.

158
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,833
Dad...

159
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:35,367
just this once, please.

160
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:39,367
At least show me...

161
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,067
that I am your child.

162
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,900
That you have even the slightest
bit of love for me.

163
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:51,633
When was the last time
you looked at me as your child?

164
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:55,200
Love?

165
00:08:56,533 --> 00:08:58,300
It's given to those
who deserve it.

166
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:02,100
It is not asked for, Edward.

167
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:03,667
And certainly not forced.

168
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,700
Then what about Paolo?

169
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,600
No matter what he does,
even if he messes up,

170
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:09,567
you are always there
to help him.

171
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:13,467
But me, whatever I do...

172
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:16,533
Is it because I am weak?

173
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:18,433
Because I make mistakes...

174
00:09:18,567 --> 00:09:21,133
you punish me my whole life?

175
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:29,567
What did I do to you to make you
treat me like trash?

176
00:09:29,733 --> 00:09:33,167
You treat me
like I'm not your own child!

177
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,500
Do you want to know why?

178
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:39,100
- Greg, stop!
- No, Mom!

179
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:41,133
Let him speak! Go ahead!

180
00:09:41,267 --> 00:09:42,300
I want to know!

181
00:09:42,433 --> 00:09:46,900
I want to know why you cannot
see me as your child.

182
00:09:47,033 --> 00:09:48,733
You want the truth?

183
00:09:48,867 --> 00:09:51,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:09:58,067 --> 00:09:59,833
Greg, please!

185
00:09:59,967 --> 00:10:01,400
Please, do not go through
with this, Greg.

186
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:03,500
Please, I am begging you.

187
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,067
[SOBBING]

188
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,200
You will get nothing from us!

189
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:11,033
Leave now!

190
00:10:11,167 --> 00:10:12,867
- Dad...
- I might do something worse

191
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:13,867
to you.

192
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:14,967
Dad!

193
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,900
Ashley's life is at stake here!

194
00:10:18,033 --> 00:10:19,867
My child's life!

195
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,767
Your grandchild's life!

196
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,567
Please have mercy on her!

197
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:25,367
Even if you turn the world
upside down,

198
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,000
she is still a Torrecampo.

199
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:29,667
Have mercy on her, Dad!

200
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,067
Grandchild?

201
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:36,733
Maybe you are forgetting
who that child's mother is.

202
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:41,900
I feel no love.

203
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:46,800
Even more so, I will not
waste anything...

204
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,700
helping the child of a mistress.

205
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,133
Is that really how it is?

206
00:10:51,267 --> 00:10:52,567
Is this because of Thea?

207
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:57,133
Because Ashley came
from Paolo's betrayal,

208
00:10:57,267 --> 00:10:58,867
you will let her die?

209
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,133
Dad, you are heartless!

210
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:06,733
You're heartless!

211
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,867
Think whatever you want.

212
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,867
But I will never help someone

213
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,867
who should never have been part
of this family!

214
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,367
Go!

215
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,633
Edward!

216
00:11:27,767 --> 00:11:30,733
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

217
00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:32,000
What?

218
00:11:32,133 --> 00:11:33,267
Let him be!

219
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:39,600
Edward!

220
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:41,000
Edward, wait!

221
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,800
Edward!

222
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:44,033
Stay away from this, Marj,

223
00:11:44,167 --> 00:11:45,667
if you do not want to get caught
in dad's anger.

224
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:50,500
Edward, Paolo and I
will take care of Ashley.

225
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:54,600
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,467
Did you not hear dad?

227
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,067
If you help me,

228
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,167
you will pay for it.

229
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:04,833
And besides,

230
00:12:04,967 --> 00:12:06,867
I do not want to be indebted
to Paolo.

231
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,067
Edward, this is not a debt.

232
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:13,767
This is help and gratitude
for what Ashley did for Jasmine.

233
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,567
I do not know why your father
treats you this way.

234
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:19,233
That makes the two of us.

235
00:12:20,267 --> 00:12:22,000
I want you to know that
you do not deserve

236
00:12:22,133 --> 00:12:23,867
to be treated like this.

237
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,533
You are a good parent
and a good child.

238
00:12:27,567 --> 00:12:29,000
You deserve better.

239
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:33,100
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:34,267
Thank you.

241
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,333
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,133
Okay, thank you, Doctor.

243
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,267
Excuse me.

244
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,700
[SIGHS]

245
00:12:53,267 --> 00:12:55,800
Why? What happened?

246
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:59,233
The infection is spreading
in Ashley's back.

247
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:02,167
She needs surgery now.

248
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,233
Schedule Ashley's surgery now.

249
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:06,967
I already paid.

250
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,433
Only the schedule is missing.

251
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:10,067
What did I tell you?

252
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:13,300
Thea, please, we did not
come here to fight.

253
00:13:13,433 --> 00:13:15,567
So please don't push us away.

254
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:19,333
We want to help Ashley.

255
00:13:19,467 --> 00:13:22,500
Let us make peace,
for the sake of the children.

256
00:13:22,667 --> 00:13:24,867
Make peace?

257
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,500
Just because you paid
for Ashley's surgery,

258
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:29,567
we're just going to forget
about what happened?

259
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,767
That is not even enough
for how much you wronged us!

260
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:34,467
- Thea, enough!
- No!

261
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:37,933
What they did is not enough!

262
00:13:38,967 --> 00:13:41,300
I will continue the case
against you.

263
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:43,833
And I will not stop
until you are imprisoned.

264
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:45,600
I told you to stop!

265
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:47,133
Why?

266
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:49,800
Are you afraid now?

267
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:52,300
Do not tell me
you still consider them family

268
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:53,700
after everything.

269
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,333
Even when they despise you!

270
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,200
I am thinking about Ashley.

271
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:59,633
I am thinking about our peace.

272
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:03,067
Now, if you still insist...

273
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:06,200
Ashley and I will leave you.

274
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:09,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:27,000
I should not have done it, Pao.

276
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,800
What are you talking about?

277
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,500
The Menagerie project before,

278
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:38,467
I helped Aldrin to sabotage
your project.

279
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:42,067
And recently, I also spoke
to the board members...

280
00:14:43,533 --> 00:14:45,033
to replace you with Aldrin.

281
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:50,233
None of the company stuff
matters right now.

282
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,833
Our children getting sick...

283
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:57,600
I think it is God's way
of telling us

284
00:14:59,167 --> 00:15:02,233
to focus on what truly matters.

285
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,400
Our relationship
with our family.

286
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:10,933
But, Pao, if dad finds out

287
00:15:11,067 --> 00:15:13,767
- that you are helping me...
- He does not have to know.

288
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,933
I used to think...

289
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:22,033
you were like dad.

290
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,900
Now I realize you are not.

291
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:28,467
Because you were there
when it truly mattered.

292
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:32,633
Maybe if you were the one
to approach dad,

293
00:15:32,767 --> 00:15:34,667
he would not refuse you.

294
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,767
Because I get rejected
immediately.

295
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:41,833
As if I am not his child.

296
00:15:41,967 --> 00:15:42,933
Only you.

297
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:46,100
I don't understand why.

298
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,833
If there is one thing
I am sure of...

299
00:15:53,633 --> 00:15:54,800
from now on,

300
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:58,033
I will be that person for you.

301
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:03,100
What?

302
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:06,133
The person you can rely on.
No questions asked.

303
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:09,333
One word from you,
and I will give full support.

304
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,000
One hundred percent.

305
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:12,867
You won't need
to repeat yourself.

306
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:27,333
I am not saying this
because you might sue us.

307
00:16:27,467 --> 00:16:30,667
Or because I owe Ashley.

308
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,467
Or to you.

309
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:38,500
I am saying this

310
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:39,900
because it is true.

311
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,800
You are my only brother.

312
00:16:43,933 --> 00:16:46,867
And I will never abandon you.

313
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

314
00:16:59,367 --> 00:17:01,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:04,067
This is wrong.

316
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,333
Did you not think about
the employees

317
00:17:07,467 --> 00:17:09,833
before you decided to push
through with that project?

318
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:12,533
Cynthia?

319
00:17:12,667 --> 00:17:13,967
Ronald? Paul?

320
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:16,500
What?

321
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:19,200
They will be affected the most.

322
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:21,133
They will lose their jobs

323
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:24,433
once the people
from Washington Builders

324
00:17:24,567 --> 00:17:26,667
enter this company.

325
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,233
Do you understand that?

326
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:33,633
We have to make
the necessary sacrifices

327
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:36,200
if we want the company
to profit.

328
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,733
They are not objects

329
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:44,333
that can just be discarded

330
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:46,600
when you no longer need them.

331
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,133
Some of them have been with
the company for a long time.

332
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:51,933
You know that!

333
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:54,000
They are practically family.

334
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:57,533
Well...

335
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:02,133
if from the very beginning

336
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:04,500
you had run the company
properly,

337
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:07,933
we would not be
in this situation.

338
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,767
But what actually happened?

339
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:11,167
It was neglected.

340
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:15,667
So, where is that family
you keep talking about?

341
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:19,033
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

342
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:28,767
You are not the only one
who gets to decide this, Aldrin.

343
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:34,167
Let us put it to a vote

344
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:36,267
on whether we continue
with that project.

345
00:18:41,533 --> 00:18:42,967
Let us vote.

346
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:46,400
Who is in favor?

347
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:48,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:58,500
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:19:16,667 --> 00:19:20,300
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

350
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:31,567
Mom, Dad, after this,

351
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:34,700
once I can walk again,

352
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:38,833
let's travel abroad, okay?

353
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:42,933
Like the plan we had
back when we were in Cebu.

354
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:45,767
Yes, my child.

355
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,733
We will do that.

356
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:51,300
Just promise me one thing.

357
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:53,000
That you will fight in there.

358
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:56,733
And that you will get better.

359
00:19:56,867 --> 00:19:58,400
We will wait for you,
my child.

360
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:01,400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:05,767
We will go anywhere you want,
my child.

362
00:20:07,233 --> 00:20:12,233
Far from the people who takes
advantage of your kindness.

363
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:17,033
And from the people
who hurt you.

364
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:19,067
Mom, please.

365
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:21,233
Do not think about that for now.

366
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:23,633
I just want...

367
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:26,267
I just want for us
to be whole again.

368
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:27,833
The three of us.

369
00:20:28,867 --> 00:20:32,067
No more anger, no more conflict.

370
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,933
Just the three of us.

371
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:37,267
Okay?

372
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:41,433
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:20:46,933 --> 00:20:48,433
Excuse me.

374
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:53,800
[SOBBING]

375
00:20:58,467 --> 00:21:00,933
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

376
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:04,533
[SOBBING]

377
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:15,300
Cheers to a successful project.

378
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:17,433
You both did great earlier.

379
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:19,300
Welcome, Sir! This way, please.

380
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:23,000
Let me prepare your table, Sir.

381
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:24,567
Excuse me.

382
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:28,333
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

383
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:32,233
Guys, excuse me for a bit.

384
00:21:34,667 --> 00:21:37,400
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

385
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:40,433
Mr. Torrecampo.

386
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:44,667
Would you care to join
the rest of the team?

387
00:21:45,867 --> 00:21:49,867
Spare me the performativity,
Mr. Castelo.

388
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,367
We do not need to be friends
outside my company.

389
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,867
I am here for business.

390
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,467
That is very understandable,
Sir Greg.

391
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,433
I know you are angry

392
00:22:03,567 --> 00:22:06,900
because aside from losing
the position of your golden boy,

393
00:22:07,033 --> 00:22:09,133
the board is siding with me.

394
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:14,133
And for that, I am truly sorry.

395
00:22:14,267 --> 00:22:16,700
I am also just here
for business.

396
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:22,000
Anyway, please tell Edward
thank you very much.

397
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,100
Why are you thanking Edward?

398
00:22:31,167 --> 00:22:34,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:22:41,633 --> 00:22:42,700
Ashley?

400
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:45,700
My child?

401
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,567
Ash!

402
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:48,933
Ash, my child.

403
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:51,533
Ash!

404
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:53,433
My child, can you hear us?

405
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:57,967
- Ash, my child!
- Mom, Dad.

406
00:22:58,100 --> 00:22:59,400
Wait, wait.

407
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:00,967
My child.

408
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:04,000
Doctor, nurse,
my child has woken up.

409
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:05,200
Please check her.

410
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,133
My child!

411
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:13,133
We are right here.

412
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:15,467
What are you feeling?

413
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,267
Does anything hurt?

414
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:19,333
Tell us, tell mommy.

415
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:25,833
Excuse me.

416
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:30,700
Ashley, how are you?

417
00:23:30,833 --> 00:23:32,567
Do you feel any pain right now?

418
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:36,067
I will just check your legs,
okay?

419
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:43,467
Can you feel this?

420
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,633
No.

421
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:48,600
How about this? Can you feel it?

422
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,900
Why?

423
00:23:54,033 --> 00:23:55,333
Did you not know?

424
00:23:57,567 --> 00:24:00,500
He was the one who convinced
the board to replace Paolo.

425
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:05,867
I would not be CEO
of Torrecampo Realty

426
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,900
if not for him.

427
00:24:10,867 --> 00:24:13,600
Anyway, I have to get back
to my team.

428
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,433
I will see you
at the contract signing.

429
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:20,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

430
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:21,700
So where were we?

431
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:27,133
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

432
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,533
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

433
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,767
Can you feel this?

434
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:40,200
No.

435
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:41,833
Can you feel this?

436
00:24:47,933 --> 00:24:50,333
Can you lift your legs for me?

437
00:24:50,467 --> 00:24:51,867
On the count of three,
one, two, three.

438
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,000
Lift.

439
00:24:56,867 --> 00:24:58,833
Okay, lift them.

440
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:03,267
How about this? Please push
your feet against my hands.

441
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,233
Mom, I cannot feel anything.

442
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:15,667
Doctor.

443
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:16,933
Doctor, what is this?

444
00:25:17,067 --> 00:25:19,067
You told me the operation
was successful!

445
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:22,067
You told me the infection
was removed from her body!

446
00:25:23,100 --> 00:25:27,733
The debilitation can still exist
even after surgery.

447
00:25:27,867 --> 00:25:30,333
Do not give me explanations
like that!

448
00:25:31,533 --> 00:25:32,967
Answer my question!

449
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:34,867
What happened?

450
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:38,067
Why can't my child
move her legs?

451
00:25:38,233 --> 00:25:42,167
You said this would be fixed!

452
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,433
You said this would be fixed!

453
00:25:43,567 --> 00:25:45,700
You promised
this would be fixed!

454
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:48,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

455
00:25:58,133 --> 00:25:59,600
Do not think
you have already won.

456
00:25:59,733 --> 00:26:01,800
I will not let you
ruin the company

457
00:26:01,933 --> 00:26:03,400
that my dad worked hard for.

458
00:26:03,533 --> 00:26:04,600
Do not be like that, Paolo.

459
00:26:04,733 --> 00:26:06,400
I know this is all new to you.

460
00:26:06,533 --> 00:26:07,667
Because you are used to winning.

461
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,133
I am just getting started.

462
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:10,667
I thought we were friends.

463
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,033
I trusted you.

464
00:26:12,167 --> 00:26:14,733
But because of you,
my family fell apart.

465
00:26:14,867 --> 00:26:17,800
What did we ever do to you
for you to destroy us?

466
00:26:17,933 --> 00:26:19,633
Your family did nothing.

467
00:26:19,767 --> 00:26:22,267
But you, you owe me.

468
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:24,633
You have the nerve
to show up here.

469
00:26:24,767 --> 00:26:27,700
If only you had treated me
like a child even once,

470
00:26:27,833 --> 00:26:29,700
I would not have turned
against you!

471
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:30,833
Do not throw that in my face.

472
00:26:30,967 --> 00:26:32,667
There is still a lot
you do not know!

473
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:33,900
I need answers, Mom.

474
00:26:34,033 --> 00:26:35,433
During my fight with dad,

475
00:26:35,567 --> 00:26:38,967
he said that there are many
things I still do not know.

476
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:40,133
Mom, what do I not know?

477
00:26:40,267 --> 00:26:42,133
You know why I am like this
toward Edward!

478
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:45,767
I know, and until now,
what you're thinking is wrong.

479
00:26:45,900 --> 00:26:49,933
Never will I accept Edward
because he is not my real child!

480
00:26:50,067 --> 00:26:51,800
He is not your blood.

481
00:26:51,933 --> 00:26:54,000
He is not a real Torrecampo.

482
00:26:54,133 --> 00:26:56,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
